{
  "video_id": "YYA113cRGO8",
  "title": "IntelÂ® Clear Containers Overview | Intel Software",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 3465.0,
      "text": "[MUSIC PLAYING]"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 5940.0,
      "end_time": 9840.0,
      "text": "Hi, I'm Amy Leland, and I\nwork at Intel's Open Source"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 9840.0,
      "end_time": 11370.0,
      "text": "Technology Center."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 11370.0,
      "end_time": 14310.0,
      "text": "I'm the program manager for\nIntel's Clear Containers"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 14310.0,
      "end_time": 15139.0,
      "text": "Project."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15139.0,
      "end_time": 17430.0,
      "text": "We're going to talk a little\nbit about what Intel Clear"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 17430.0,
      "end_time": 21030.0,
      "text": "Containers are and how they're\navailable in the ecosystem"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 21030.0,
      "end_time": 23950.0,
      "text": "today and how we integrate\nwith open source partners."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 23950.0,
      "end_time": 25980.0,
      "text": "So I'm going to start\nwith the word container."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 25980.0,
      "end_time": 30220.0,
      "text": "The word container is used for,\nreally, two separate parts."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 30220.0,
      "end_time": 32729.0,
      "text": "There's the back end\ntechnology of containers."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 32729.0,
      "end_time": 35430.0,
      "text": "So Linux kernel containers\nhave been around"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 35430.0,
      "end_time": 36980.0,
      "text": "for a really long time."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 36980.0,
      "end_time": 40250.0,
      "text": "They're about resource\nallocation and isolation."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 40250.0,
      "end_time": 43020.0,
      "text": "And the other side of that is\nthe packaging and deployment"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 43020.0,
      "end_time": 44170.0,
      "text": "of containers."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 44170.0,
      "end_time": 45990.0,
      "text": "This is what's really\nnew in the industry"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 45990.0,
      "end_time": 49710.0,
      "text": "today, which companies\nlike Docker and Brockett"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 49710.0,
      "end_time": 53160.0,
      "text": "have made container\ntechnology really easy to use."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 53160.0,
      "end_time": 56940.0,
      "text": "This is a basic diagram of\na Linux kernel container."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 56940.0,
      "end_time": 59790.0,
      "text": "And as you can\nsee, the isolation"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 59790.0,
      "end_time": 61260.0,
      "text": "is within the name-space."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 61260.0,
      "end_time": 65610.0,
      "text": "And all of the containers\nare sharing a Linux kernel."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 65610.0,
      "end_time": 69000.0,
      "text": "And while there are many\nbenefits to container"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 69000.0,
      "end_time": 72870.0,
      "text": "technology-- so they're\nfast, they're agile,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 72870.0,
      "end_time": 74400.0,
      "text": "they're easy to use--"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 74400.0,
      "end_time": 76770.0,
      "text": "there's still a lot of\nconcerns around security."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 76770.0,
      "end_time": 80130.0,
      "text": "This slide just\nsignifies that if there's"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 80130.0,
      "end_time": 84570.0,
      "text": "a kernel vulnerability that\nseeps into one container,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 84570.0,
      "end_time": 87450.0,
      "text": "it can go from one container\nto the next container"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 87450.0,
      "end_time": 90030.0,
      "text": "to the next container\nall on one host."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 90030.0,
      "end_time": 94050.0,
      "text": "Again this is due to the fact\nthat they share a Linux kernel."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 94050.0,
      "end_time": 97200.0,
      "text": "And again, this leads to\na lot of security concerns"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 97200.0,
      "end_time": 99280.0,
      "text": "in the container ecosystem."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 99280.0,
      "end_time": 103230.0,
      "text": "And as I said, I'm talking today\nabout Intel Clear Containers."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 103230.0,
      "end_time": 108120.0,
      "text": "So when we looked at\nthe container ecosystem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 108120.0,
      "end_time": 111660.0,
      "text": "we said, OK, so virtual\nmachines are secure."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 111660.0,
      "end_time": 115920.0,
      "text": "But they're slow,\nharder to manage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 115920.0,
      "end_time": 117720.0,
      "text": "and container\ntechnology-- they've"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 117720.0,
      "end_time": 121110.0,
      "text": "got all this speed, agility."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 121110.0,
      "end_time": 123060.0,
      "text": "They're very small in size."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 123060.0,
      "end_time": 125610.0,
      "text": "And can we get the\nbest of both worlds?"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 125610.0,
      "end_time": 128820.0,
      "text": "Intel Clear Containers is a\nlightweight virtual machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 128820.0,
      "end_time": 131340.0,
      "text": "So it acts as fast\nas a container,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 131340.0,
      "end_time": 134400.0,
      "text": "but it has the security\nbenefits of a virtual machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 134400.0,
      "end_time": 137220.0,
      "text": "And what we've done\nis use Intel VTX."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 137220.0,
      "end_time": 139560.0,
      "text": "So we use\nhardware-based security"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 139560.0,
      "end_time": 143640.0,
      "text": "to secure each\ncontainer on a host."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 143640.0,
      "end_time": 146580.0,
      "text": "So each container or\nlightweight virtual machine"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 146580.0,
      "end_time": 150420.0,
      "text": "has its own operating system,\nbut it's a minimal operating"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 150420.0,
      "end_time": 151380.0,
      "text": "system."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 151380.0,
      "end_time": 157050.0,
      "text": "And again, we utilize Intel\nVTX to secure each container"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 157050.0,
      "end_time": 158020.0,
      "text": "on the system."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 158020.0,
      "end_time": 161920.0,
      "text": "I always refer back to the\nfirst part of this presentation."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 161920.0,
      "end_time": 165660.0,
      "text": "So again, there's the back\nend technology of containers--"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 165660.0,
      "end_time": 167430.0,
      "text": "Linux kernel containers."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 167430.0,
      "end_time": 170250.0,
      "text": "And then there's the\nfront end application,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 170250.0,
      "end_time": 172060.0,
      "text": "logistics, deployment."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 172060.0,
      "end_time": 176280.0,
      "text": "And what we're trying to do\nis just offer another back end"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 176280.0,
      "end_time": 178140.0,
      "text": "solution in the market."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 178140.0,
      "end_time": 180870.0,
      "text": "The reality today\nis that most people"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 180870.0,
      "end_time": 184650.0,
      "text": "deploy container technology\nin a full-on virtual machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 184650.0,
      "end_time": 188220.0,
      "text": "You can see this\nas people deploy"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 188220.0,
      "end_time": 192300.0,
      "text": "on AWS or many other clouds."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 192300.0,
      "end_time": 196110.0,
      "text": "So the reality is is\nthat people are actually"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 196110.0,
      "end_time": 199650.0,
      "text": "deploying containers in\nvirtual machines already."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 199650.0,
      "end_time": 202440.0,
      "text": "What we're doing is saying,\nwhy wouldn't we just offer"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 202440.0,
      "end_time": 206760.0,
      "text": "a lightweight virtual machine\nthat, again, has the benefits,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 206760.0,
      "end_time": 210060.0,
      "text": "the security of a\nfull-on virtual machine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 210060.0,
      "end_time": 213270.0,
      "text": "but then also all of the\nbenefits that containers"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 213270.0,
      "end_time": 214050.0,
      "text": "offer--"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 214050.0,
      "end_time": 218370.0,
      "text": "size, speed, logistics, all\nthe application and deployment"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 218370.0,
      "end_time": 219420.0,
      "text": "frameworks."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 219420.0,
      "end_time": 221310.0,
      "text": "Before Intel Clear\nContainers, there"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 221310.0,
      "end_time": 222960.0,
      "text": "was really only two options."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 222960.0,
      "end_time": 226830.0,
      "text": "There's this virtual machine--\nfull-on virtual machine--"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 226830.0,
      "end_time": 230380.0,
      "text": "or a container\ntechnology solution."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 230380.0,
      "end_time": 233540.0,
      "text": "And again, we're just offering\nanother back end solution"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 233540.0,
      "end_time": 235260.0,
      "text": "into the ecosystem."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 235260.0,
      "end_time": 238920.0,
      "text": "And since Intel Clear Containers\nis a back end technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 238920.0,
      "end_time": 244320.0,
      "text": "solution, we plug into the\napplication and deployment"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 244320.0,
      "end_time": 247530.0,
      "text": "tools that you're used to\nwithin the container ecosystem."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 247530.0,
      "end_time": 250890.0,
      "text": "We plug into Docker\n1.12 and greater--"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 250890.0,
      "end_time": 253230.0,
      "text": "I think up until 1703."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 253230.0,
      "end_time": 255270.0,
      "text": "We also plug into\nnot Kubernetes."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 255270.0,
      "end_time": 258959.0,
      "text": "So you can use Intel Clear\nContainers with Kubernetes 1.5"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 258959.0,
      "end_time": 262290.0,
      "text": "and greater through\nthe CRI specification."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 262290.0,
      "end_time": 264660.0,
      "text": "We're available for Rocket 1.0."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 264660.0,
      "end_time": 268500.0,
      "text": "And we just released Intel\nClear Containers 2.1."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 268500.0,
      "end_time": 270630.0,
      "text": "It's available on Github."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 270630.0,
      "end_time": 274290.0,
      "text": "We currently package for\nmultiple Linux operating"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 274290.0,
      "end_time": 274990.0,
      "text": "systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 274990.0,
      "end_time": 278490.0,
      "text": "So this is a subset of\nLinux operating systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 278490.0,
      "end_time": 281850.0,
      "text": "We definitely don't package for\nevery single Linux operating"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 281850.0,
      "end_time": 283230.0,
      "text": "system that's out there."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 283230.0,
      "end_time": 285270.0,
      "text": "But Intel Clear\nContainers does work"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 285270.0,
      "end_time": 288330.0,
      "text": "with multiple different\nLinux distributions."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 288330.0,
      "end_time": 290580.0,
      "text": "And we have some\nrequirements that"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 290580.0,
      "end_time": 293730.0,
      "text": "are available on our\nwebsite for what's required"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 293730.0,
      "end_time": 295824.0,
      "text": "to run Intel Clear Containers."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 295824.0,
      "end_time": 297240.0,
      "text": "But you should be\nable to run them"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 297240.0,
      "end_time": 299280.0,
      "text": "with any Linux\ndistribution, as long as you"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 299280.0,
      "end_time": 301000.0,
      "text": "follow those guidelines."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 301000.0,
      "end_time": 303800.0,
      "text": "So there's a lot of\ncontainer specifications"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 303800.0,
      "end_time": 305290.0,
      "text": "that are out there today."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 305290.0,
      "end_time": 309310.0,
      "text": "And we try to work both\nupstream and downstream."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 309310.0,
      "end_time": 311040.0,
      "text": "And so I'm going to\ntalk through that."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 311040.0,
      "end_time": 312510.0,
      "text": "The Open Container Initiative--"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 312510.0,
      "end_time": 315820.0,
      "text": "OCI-- is one specification\nthat's out there."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 315820.0,
      "end_time": 318700.0,
      "text": "And we are compliant\nwith that specification."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 318700.0,
      "end_time": 321450.0,
      "text": "We also are compliant\nwith APPC, which"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 321450.0,
      "end_time": 325270.0,
      "text": "is another specification\nin the container ecosystem."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 325270.0,
      "end_time": 328020.0,
      "text": "We are compliant with CRI--"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 328020.0,
      "end_time": 330120.0,
      "text": "the Container\nRuntime Interface--"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 330120.0,
      "end_time": 332280.0,
      "text": "that Google and Red Hat started."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 332280.0,
      "end_time": 334110.0,
      "text": "And this is the\nprimary interface"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 334110.0,
      "end_time": 338490.0,
      "text": "to work with Kubernetes,\nwhich I talked about earlier."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 338490.0,
      "end_time": 342000.0,
      "text": "We have also added support\nfor Intel Clear Containers"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 342000.0,
      "end_time": 344650.0,
      "text": "in the container\nnetworking space."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 344650.0,
      "end_time": 347920.0,
      "text": "So there's two specifications\nthat are out there today."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 347920.0,
      "end_time": 349800.0,
      "text": "There's CNI and CNN."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 349800.0,
      "end_time": 353520.0,
      "text": "And we've added the\nability to support"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 353520.0,
      "end_time": 357150.0,
      "text": "lightweight virtual machines\nin those specifications."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 357150.0,
      "end_time": 361340.0,
      "text": "So again, we're available\nfor both CNI and CNN."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 361340.0,
      "end_time": 363930.0,
      "text": "And in terms of\ndownstream proliferation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 363930.0,
      "end_time": 367650.0,
      "text": "we're working with the likes\nof Docker, Rocket, Kubernetes"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 367650.0,
      "end_time": 370380.0,
      "text": "to be integrated within\nthose communities."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 370380.0,
      "end_time": 372550.0,
      "text": "But we also want to\npartner with companies--"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 372550.0,
      "end_time": 376410.0,
      "text": "OSV's, ISV's,\nIntegrators, and CSP's--"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 376410.0,
      "end_time": 378870.0,
      "text": "to offer go-to-market solutions."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 378870.0,
      "end_time": 381320.0,
      "text": "Intel Clear Containers\nis an open source project"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 381320.0,
      "end_time": 384150.0,
      "text": "that Intel is a part of."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 384150.0,
      "end_time": 386850.0,
      "text": "And again, we want to\nwork with our partners"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 386850.0,
      "end_time": 389310.0,
      "text": "to offer go-to-market solutions."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 389310.0,
